  "plan_analysis": "The pre-research gives only a May-2024 snapshot and the mechanical rules of the rankings.  A forecaster still needs:\n\n1. Current state: Who is #1 in March 2026 and with how many points?  What are the point totals of the other contenders?\n2. Key upcoming events before 27 Apr 2026: Indian Wells, Miami, Monte-Carlo, Barcelona, start of Madrid\u2014plus any injuries or withdrawals that could alter outcomes.\n3. Base rate / historical context: Typical #1 point totals in late April across many years and how much they tend to move between early March and late April.\n4. Defending-points picture: How many points the current leaders must defend in the next seven weeks.\n5. Contrarian signals: Injury news or schedule changes that could suddenly limit a front-runner or enable a challenger.\n\nThe search strategy therefore collects:\n\u2022 Historical #1 point totals around late-April and season-end to build a distribution.\n\u2022 Current 2026 rankings and Race standings for momentum.\n\u2022 Tournament-by-tournament defending-points data and injury/withdrawal news for the leading players.\n\u2022 Analyses of how much the clay-court swing usually shifts point totals.",
